 view to fit your applications profile."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Customize loading, preloading and error views."}],"title":"Customize views to fit your application","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/customizingviews","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/CustomizingViews","estimatedTime":"3min"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/RemoteSnippet":{"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to set up a manager to handle the logic and functionality of your snippets, as well as how to seamlessly integrate them into your SwiftUI views.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/RemoteSnippet","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/remotesnippet","title":"Display your first remote snippet","role":"project","estimatedTime":"3min","type":"topic"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/LocalSnippet":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/LocalSnippet","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/localsnippet","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"2min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to work with TWS snippets locally without connecting to our backend service. This tutorial will guide you through the steps to display a webpage snippet in your app, bypassing the backend, and focusing solely on rendering and showcasing the snippet content."}],"type":"topic","title":"Display your first local snippet","role":"project"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/Notifications#Integrating-TWSNotifications":{"type":"section","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/Notifications#Integrating-TWSNotifications","abstract":[{"text":"In this tutorial you will learn how to easily integrate TWSNotifications in your existing push notification code base.","type":"text"}],"title":"Integrating TWSNotifications","kind":"section","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/notifications#Integrating-TWSNotifications","role":"pseudoSymbol"},"CustomizingViews_03.swift":{"type":"file","highlights":[],"fileType":"swift","content":["import Foundatio